(81, 2, '2019-04-23 03:54:47', '2019-04-23 03:54:47', '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>\n\nThe grandest festival in Zamboanga is already a few months away! Zamboanga Hermosa Festival, also known as Fiesta Pilar, is one of the oldest and most colorful festivals in the country. The festival is held every October in honor of the city\'s patroness, Nuestra Seora La Virgen del Pilar. The month-long festivities will kick off on October 1 with the Grand Parade and Opening Salvo at the Mayor Vitaliano Agan Coliseum at 3PM. Here\'s the first look and feels of this year\'s festival.\n\n</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":78} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"http://localhost/zamboangacity.gov.ph/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/Zamboanga-Hermosa-Festival-2018-Streetdance-1024x585.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-78\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>\n\nA wide array of events are lined up in the following days leading to the feast day on October 12. Some of the highlights include the Regatta de Zamboanga, Parade of Lights (Float Competition), Mascota de Zamboanga, and the Streetdance Competition. Check out below the Calendar of major activities prepared by the City Government of Zamboanga.\n\n</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":79} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"http://localhost/zamboangacity.gov.ph/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/Zamboanga-Hermosa-Festival-2018-Calendarsq-03-1024x799.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-79\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Zamboanga Hermosa Festival 2018 Calendar of Activities</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Inter-Barangay Fiesta Arco Competition<br>September 22 (Saturday), Participating Barangays</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Badminton Tournament<br>September 28-30 (Friday-Saturday), Summit Centre, Tetuan</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Zambassadors Mall Tour ft. Original Chavacano Video Music Festival 2018 Grand Launching&nbsp;<br>September 29, 6PM, Saturday, CityMall Tetuan and KCC Mall de Zamboanga</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Smoke Out Zamboanga  Grilled Food Fiesta and Zamboanga Grand Midnight Sale<br>September 29October 13 (SaturdaySaturday), R.T. Lim Boulevard</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Zamboanga Art Exhibit 2018<br>September 30October 14 (SundayMonday)</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Cosechas de Zamboanga 2018&nbsp;<br>October 115, (MondayFriday), Plaza Pershing</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Hermosa Heritage Zone Walking Tour<br>October 1-11 (Monday-Thursday), City Tourism Office, Paseo del Mar</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Hermosa Festival Opening Salvo ft. Inter-Barangay Bandoreal Competition and Pink Parade<br>October 1 (Monday), 3PM, City Coliseum, Tetuan</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>5th Conferencia de Historia, Cultura y Artes de Zamboanga<br>October 2-4, (Tuesday-Thursday), 8AM, Centro Latino, Paseo del Mar</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Pet Parade and Blessing<br>October 4 (Thursday), 4PM, Jardin Maria Clara, Pasonanca</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>ZC Travel and Tour Expo<br>October 5-7 (Friday-Sunday), 9AM-9PM, Centro Latino, Paseo del Mar</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Copa de Ciudad Fiesta Pilar Open Invitational Bowling Tournament 2018<br>October 5-7 (Friday-Sunday) Tebi &amp; Sean Recreational Center</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>2nd Zamboanga Hermosa Pencak Silat Invitational Tournament 2018<br>October 5-7 (Friday-Sunday) KCC Mall de Zamboanga</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>4th La Hermosa Invitational Volleyball Tournament 2018<br>October 5-7 (Friday-Sunday) City Coliseum/Sta Maria Elementary Covered Court</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Noche de Bailes y Canciones&nbsp;<br>October 6 (Saturday), 7PM, National Museum</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Zamboanga Hermosa Festival Chess Championship 2018<br>October 6-7 (Saturday-Sunday) KCC Mall de Zamboanga</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>3rd Zamboanga Hermosa Festival Sepatakraw Tournament 2018<br>October 6-7 (Saturday-Sunday)Zamboanga City State Polytechnic College (ZCSPC)</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Zamboanga Hermosa Primer Juego de Nadada 2018<br>October 6-7 (Saturday-Sunday) JFEMSC Grandstand Swimming Pool</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>2018 Regional Inter-school Taekwondo Championship Zamboanga Hermosa Festival<br>October 6-7 (Saturday-Sunday) KCC Mall de Zamboanga</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Hermosa Cup 2018 Invitational Table Tennis Tournament<br>October 6-7 (Saturday-Sunday) City Mall Tetuan</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>2nd Zamboanga Hermosa Weightlifting Open Championship 2018<br>October 6-7 (Saturday-Sunday) JFEMSC Grandstand, Baliwasan</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>1st Zamboanga Hermosa Festival Philspada Sports Tournament 2018<br>October 6-7 (Saturday-Sunday) Grandstand / City Coliseum</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>La Gran Procesion de la Santas Imagenes<br>October 6-7 (Saturday-Sunday) ADZU Grounds to Fort Pilar</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Sandy Jamiro: Zamboanguea Pintor<br>October 6-27 (Saturday-Saturday) Garden Orchid Hotel Lobby&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Fit to Fight: A Breast Cancer Zumba Dance Party<br>October 7 (Sunday), 6PM, Paseo del Mar</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Zamboanga Dancesport Competition<br>October 8 (Monday), 1PM, City Coliseum, Tetuan</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Original Chavacano Video Music Festival 2018<br>October 8 (Monday), 7PM, Centro Latino, Paseo del Mar</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Mascota de Zamboanga Competition 2018&nbsp;<br>October 9 (Tuesday), 7PM, Palacio del Sur</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Regatta de Zamboanga 2018<br>October 10 (Wednesday), 7AM, R.T. Lim Boulevard</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Wow Sardinas Grand Boodle Fight<br>October 10 (Wednesday), 11AM, R.T. Lim Boulevard</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Parade of Lights (Float Competition)<br>October 10 (Wednesday), 6PM, Mayor Vitaliano Agan Ave (former Nuez Extension) to City Hall Grounds</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Concierto na Ayuntamiento<br>October 10 (Wednesday), 6PM, City Hall Grounds</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Zamboanga Hermosa Streetdance Competition &amp; Fiesta Main Program<br>October 11 (Thursday), 8AM</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Balik Zamboanga Night<br>October 11 (Thursday), 7PM, Patio Palmeras</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Feast of Our Lady Of The Pillar<br>October 12 (Friday), Fort Pilar Shrine</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Danza La Vida (Street Party)<br>October 13 (Saturday), 7PM</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Hermosa Photography Competition 2018<br>October 19 (Friday), 5PM  Deadline of Submission<br>October 21 (Sunday),11AM  Exhibit Opening<br>October 28 (Saturday), 11AM&nbsp;&nbsp;Awarding Ceremony</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>More events will be included in the coming weeks so like the official facebook page&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/ZamboHermosaFestival2014/\">Zamboanga Hermosa Festival</a>&nbsp;to get the latest updates. Follow us on Twitter (<a href=\"https://twitter.com/zambocitygovt\">@zambocitygovt</a>) and Instagram (<a href=\"https://www.instagram.com/zambocitygovt/\">@zambocitygovt</a>), and subscribe the Youtube Channel&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/channel/UC6UTqc23vwgs_oCehgeQ0sw\">Zamboanga City Official</a>. Share and invite your friends this October to experience the most colorful festival of the south! Use the official hashtags: #ZamboHermosaFest and #iLoveZamboangaCity.&nbsp;\n\n</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":80} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"http://localhost/zamboangacity.gov.ph/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/Zamboanga-Hermosa-Festival-2018-1024x1024.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-80\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->', 'Zamboanga Hermosa Festival 2018 Calendar of Activities', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '77-revision-v1', '', '', '2019-04-23 03:54:47', '2019-04-23 03:54:47', '', 77, 'http://localhost/zamboangacity.gov.ph/77-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(82, 2, '2019-04-23 03:57:17', '2019-04-23 03:57:17', '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Welcome to WordPress. This is your first post. Edit or delete it, then start writing!</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', 'Hello world!', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '1-revision-v1', '', '', '2019-04-23 03:57:17', '2019-04-23 03:57:17', '', 1, 'http://localhost/zamboangacity.gov.ph/1-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(83, 2, '2019-04-23 03:59:06', '2019-04-23 03:59:06', '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>International Women\'s Day (IWD) is celebrated annually on March 8.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The day has occurred for well over a century, with the first IWD gathering in 1911.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The day is not country, group or organization specific - and belongs to all groups collectively everywhere.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Gloria Steinem, world-renowned feminist, journalist and activist&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.internationalwomensday.com/External.aspx?u=https://www.seattletimes.com/opinion/herersquos-to-the-memory-of-gloria-steinem-and-the-other-women-who-struggled-for-equality/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\"><strong>once explained</strong></a>&nbsp;\"The story of women\'s struggle for equality belongs to no single feminist nor to any one organization but to the collective efforts of all who care about human rights.\"</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>So make International Women\'s Day your day and do what you can to truly make a positive difference for women.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":84} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"http://localhost/zamboangacity.gov.ph/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/about-iwd.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-84\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3>What is International Women\'s Day?</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>International Women\'s Day (March 8) is a global day celebrating the social, economic, cultural and political achievements of women. The day also marks a call to action for accelerating gender parity.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>No one government, NGO, charity, corporation, academic institution, women\'s network or media hub is solely responsible for International Women\'s Day. Many organizations declare an annual IWD theme that supports their specific agenda or cause, and some of these are adopted more widely with relevance than others. International Women\'s Day is a collective day of global celebration and a call for gender parity.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>International Women\'s Day is all about unity, celebration, reflection, advocacy and action - whatever that looks like globally at a local level. But one thing is for sure, International Women\'s Day has been occurring for well over a century - and continue\'s to grow from strength to strength. Learn about the&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.internationalwomensday.com/Values\"><strong>values</strong></a>&nbsp;that guide IWD\'s ethos.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3>What colours signify International Women\'s Day?</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Internationally, purple is a colour for symbolising women. Historically the combination of purple, green and white to symbolise women\'s equality originated from the Women\'s Social and Political Union in the UK in 1908. Purple signifies justice and dignity. Green symbolises hope. White represents purity, but is no longer used due to \'purity\' being a controversial concept.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', 'About International Women\'s Day', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'about-international-womens-day', '', '', '2019-04-23 03:59:06', '2019-04-23 03:59:06', '', 0, 'http://localhost/zamboangacity.gov.ph/?p=83', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(84, 2, '2019-04-23 03:58:59', '2019-04-23 03:58:59', '', 'about-iwd', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', 'about-iwd', '', '', '2019-04-23 03:58:59', '2019-04-23 03:58:59', '', 83, 'http://localhost/zamboangacity.gov.ph/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/about-iwd.png', 0, 'attachment', 'image/png', 0),
