(150, 2, '2019-04-24 02:54:45', '2019-04-24 02:54:45', '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>City Government of Zamboanga</strong><br>Zamboanga City Hall, NS Valderrosa Street<br>Zamboanga City</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Telephone : (062) 992-0420 | 991-4525<br>Email Address : zambocitygovt@gmail.com</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:shortcode -->\n[su_box title=\"Box title\" style=\"default\" box_color=\"#e90477\" title_color=\"#FFFFFF\" radius=\"3\" class=\"\"][contact-form-7 id=\"120\" title=\"Contact form 1\"][/su_box]\n<!-- /wp:shortcode -->\n\n<!-- wp:separator -->\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator\"/>\n<!-- /wp:separator -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', 'Contact Us', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '17-revision-v1', '', '', '2019-04-24 02:54:45', '2019-04-24 02:54:45', '', 17, 'http://localhost/zamboangacity.gov.ph/17-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(151, 2, '2019-04-24 02:57:11', '2019-04-24 02:57:11', '<!-- wp:shortcode -->\n[su_accordion class=\"\"]\n  [su_spoiler title=\"How\'s the event?\" open=\"no\" style=\"default\" icon=\"plus\" anchor=\"\" class=\"\"]It\'s awesome![/su_spoiler]\n  [su_spoiler title=\"When will be the second event?\" open=\"no\" style=\"default\" icon=\"plus\" anchor=\"\" class=\"\"]This will be announce![/su_spoiler]\n[/su_accordion]\n<!-- /wp:shortcode -->', 'Frequently Asked Questions', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '31-revision-v1', '', '', '2019-04-24 02:57:11', '2019-04-24 02:57:11', '', 31, 'http://localhost/zamboangacity.gov.ph/31-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(152, 2, '2019-04-24 06:30:02', '2019-04-24 06:30:02', '<!-- wp:shortcode -->\n[su_accordion class=\"\"]\n  [su_spoiler title=\"How\'s the event?\" open=\"no\" style=\"default\" icon=\"plus\" anchor=\"\" class=\"\"]It\'s awesome![/su_spoiler]\n  [su_spoiler title=\"When will be the second event?\" open=\"no\" style=\"default\" icon=\"plus\" anchor=\"\" class=\"\"]This will be announce![/su_spoiler]\n [su_spoiler title=\"Where to stay in Zamboanga?\" open=\"no\" style=\"default\" icon=\"plus\" anchor=\"\" class=\"\"]\n1. Garden Orchid Hotel<br>\n2. Grand Astoria Hotel<br>\n3. Ever O Business Hotel<br>\n4. City Inn Hotel<br>\n5. Winzelle Suites<br>\n6. Casa Canelar Pension<br>[/su_spoiler]\n[/su_accordion]\n\n\n \n<!-- /wp:shortcode -->', 'Frequently Asked Questions', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '31-revision-v1', '', '', '2019-04-24 06:30:02', '2019-04-24 06:30:02', '', 31, 'http://localhost/zamboangacity.gov.ph/31-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(153, 2, '2019-04-24 06:36:27', '2019-04-24 06:36:27', '<!-- wp:shortcode -->\n[su_accordion class=\"\"]\n\n[su_spoiler title=\"How\'s the event?\" open=\"no\" style=\"default\" icon=\"plus\" anchor=\"\" class=\"\"]It\'s awesome![/su_spoiler]\n\n[su_spoiler title=\"When will be the second event?\" open=\"no\" style=\"default\" icon=\"plus\" anchor=\"\" class=\"\"]This will be announce![/su_spoiler]\n\n[su_spoiler title=\"Where to stay in Zamboanga?\" open=\"no\" style=\"default\" icon=\"plus\" anchor=\"\" class=\"\"]\n1. Garden Orchid Hotel<br>\n2. Grand Astoria Hotel<br>\n3. Ever O Business Hotel<br>\n4. City Inn Hotel<br>\n5. Winzelle Suites<br>\n6. Casa Canelar Pension<br>[/su_spoiler]\n[/su_accordion]\n\n[su_spoiler title=\"what to see?\" open=\"no\" style=\"default\" icon=\"plus\" anchor=\"\" class=\"\"]\nThe city prides itself as one of the oldest city in the country that progressively transitioned from the 16th century to the present age of modernity. Zamboanga is a city of rich Hispanic culture. A glimpse of the glory and spectrum of our proud history can be well reminisced thru the landmarks and historical sites that defines the unique and treasured heritage of the city. <br>\n1. City Hall\n2. Fort Pilar\n3. Mayor Cesar C. Climaco Freedom Park\n4. Merloquet Falls\n5. Paseo del Mar\n6. Pasonanca Park\n7. Plaza del Pilar\n8. Plaza Pershing\n9. Sta. Cruz Island\n10. Taluksangay Mosque\n11. Yakan Weaving Village\n12. Zamboanga Golf Course\n[/su_spoiler]\n\n \n<!-- /wp:shortcode -->', 'Frequently Asked Questions', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '31-revision-v1', '', '', '2019-04-24 06:36:27', '2019-04-24 06:36:27', '', 31, 'http://localhost/zamboangacity.gov.ph/31-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(154, 2, '2019-04-24 06:37:08', '2019-04-24 06:37:08', '<!-- wp:shortcode -->\n[su_accordion class=\"\"]\n\n[su_spoiler title=\"How\'s the event?\" open=\"no\" style=\"default\" icon=\"plus\" anchor=\"\" class=\"\"]It\'s awesome![/su_spoiler]\n\n[su_spoiler title=\"When will be the second event?\" open=\"no\" style=\"default\" icon=\"plus\" anchor=\"\" class=\"\"]This will be announce![/su_spoiler]\n\n[su_spoiler title=\"Where to stay in Zamboanga?\" open=\"no\" style=\"default\" icon=\"plus\" anchor=\"\" class=\"\"]\n1. Garden Orchid Hotel<br>\n2. Grand Astoria Hotel<br>\n3. Ever O Business Hotel<br>\n4. City Inn Hotel<br>\n5. Winzelle Suites<br>\n6. Casa Canelar Pension<br>[/su_spoiler]\n[/su_accordion]\n\n[su_spoiler title=\"what to see?\" open=\"no\" style=\"default\" icon=\"plus\" anchor=\"\" class=\"\"]\nThe city prides itself as one of the oldest city in the country that progressively transitioned from the 16th century to the present age of modernity. Zamboanga is a city of rich Hispanic culture. A glimpse of the glory and spectrum of our proud history can be well reminisced thru the landmarks and historical sites that defines the unique and treasured heritage of the city. <br>\n1. City Hall <br>\n2. Fort Pilar <br>\n3. Mayor Cesar C. Climaco Freedom Park <br>\n4. Merloquet Falls <br>\n5. Paseo del Mar <br>\n6. Pasonanca Park <br>\n7. Plaza del Pilar <br>\n8. Plaza Pershing <br>\n9. Sta. Cruz Island <br>\n10. Taluksangay Mosque <br>\n11. Yakan Weaving Village <br>\n12. Zamboanga Golf Course \n[/su_spoiler]\n\n \n<!-- /wp:shortcode -->', 'Frequently Asked Questions', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '31-revision-v1', '', '', '2019-04-24 06:37:08', '2019-04-24 06:37:08', '', 31, 'http://localhost/zamboangacity.gov.ph/31-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(156, 2, '2019-04-24 06:41:11', '2019-04-24 06:41:11', '<!-- wp:shortcode -->\n[su_accordion class=\"\"]\n\n[su_spoiler title=\"How\'s the event?\" open=\"no\" style=\"default\" icon=\"plus\" anchor=\"\" class=\"\"]It\'s awesome![/su_spoiler]\n\n[su_spoiler title=\"When will be the second event?\" open=\"no\" style=\"default\" icon=\"plus\" anchor=\"\" class=\"\"]This will be announce![/su_spoiler]\n\n[su_spoiler title=\"Where to stay in Zamboanga?\" open=\"no\" style=\"default\" icon=\"plus\" anchor=\"\" class=\"\"]\n1. Garden Orchid Hotel<br>\n2. Grand Astoria Hotel<br>\n3. Ever O Business Hotel<br>\n4. City Inn Hotel<br>\n5. Winzelle Suites<br>\n6. Casa Canelar Pension<br>\n[/su_spoiler]\n\n\n[su_spoiler title=\"what to see?\" open=\"no\" style=\"default\" icon=\"plus\" anchor=\"\" class=\"\"]\nThe city prides itself as one of the oldest city in the country that progressively transitioned from the 16th century to the present age of modernity. Zamboanga is a city of rich Hispanic culture. A glimpse of the glory and spectrum of our proud history can be well reminisced thru the landmarks and historical sites that defines the unique and treasured heritage of the city. <br>\n1. City Hall <br>\n2. Fort Pilar <br>\n3. Mayor Cesar C. Climaco Freedom Park <br>\n4. Merloquet Falls <br>\n5. Paseo del Mar <br>\n6. Pasonanca Park <br>\n7. Plaza del Pilar <br>\n8. Plaza Pershing <br>\n9. Sta. Cruz Island <br>\n10. Taluksangay Mosque <br>\n11. Yakan Weaving Village <br>\n12. Zamboanga Golf Course \n[/su_spoiler]\n\n[su_spoiler title=\"When will be the second event?\" open=\"no\" style=\"default\" icon=\"plus\" anchor=\"\" class=\"\"]\nThe food capital of Zamboanga Peninsula, one can have the best gastronomic experience with the fusion of flavors that the local cuisines and delicacies offer. While in Zamboanga, feast on a wide array of seafood cuisines such as the famous Curacha, the red-meaty crab found solely in the deep waters of Zamboanga. Likewise try the Seafood Paella and other seafood cuisines to complete your seafood fiesta. And, if possible, dont miss Satti, a southern delicacy that comes in tamo (rice steamed in coconut leaves) and skewers of beef or chicken served in a bowl of Sambal (thick hot & spicy sauce). Satti is best eaten as breakfast, a perfect way to start your day in Zamboanga City.\n\n1. Alavar Seafoods House\n2. Baytalmal Restaurant\n3. Chinitos\n4. Country Chicken\n5. Hacienda Palmeras Hotel and Restaurant\n6. Hanazono Japanese Restaurant\n7. Sunflower Food Center\n8. ZC Haisan Seafood Restaurant\n[/su_spoiler]\n\n[/su_accordion]\n \n<!-- /wp:shortcode -->', 'Frequently Asked Questions', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '31-revision-v1', '', '', '2019-04-24 06:41:11', '2019-04-24 06:41:11', '', 31, 'http://localhost/zamboangacity.gov.ph/31-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
